
This is where ObsidianWall starts transitioning from:

> “policy evaluator”

into:

> “infrastructure intelligence system.”

And your instinct is correct:

Right now your recommendation and optimization layers are still mostly:

# static heuristics

Meaning:

```python
if estimated_cost > 50:
```

or:

```python
if "aws_instance" in resource_type:
```

That is rule-based advisory logic.

Good MVP architecture.
Not yet advanced infrastructure intelligence.

